one day a panda walks into a chines bar, and says " Gimme some Bambo!" so you know, the waiter, not wanting to be mauled by a panda BEAR goes and gets Mr. Panda-Poo some bamboo. the panda eats it, pulls out a semi-automatic, and shoots the waiter dead!!!! (which is pretty cool, because pandas don't have thumbs, so he's pretty cool!) anyways, the next day, the panda comes back, and does the same thing. this becomes a trend, and each day, Mr. Panda-Poo comes in, and eats bambo, shoots the waiter and leaves. can't you see the headlines now? "multipul time murdering panda still at large"? i can. anyways, so about a week into this horrible killing spree, the mangager of the chines place comes and has a little talk with the panda. why it took him this long i don't know, i guess he was worried for his own safety. well so he guy asks Mr. panda-Poo why he's killing all his waiters, and the panda says "Look me up in the dictionary" so, you know, they guy does, and it says "panda-N, eats bambo, shoots, and leaves" hahahahahahahahaha

WEll, now let me see, Im gonna talk to you about the romans. I know you all are very familar with them, but I don't care. I think that the romans were crazy. Think about this: the diameter of the Saturn5 rocket, you know the one that took us to the moon, was directly related the the diameter of two roman horse's asses, because the roman's built their roads wide enough to hold a chariot , and the chariot size was dictated but the two horse ass diamter. Well when railroads were first build they made them uniform, and set the to the size of the old roman roads. (they were easy to build over) So the size of our railroads were the same as the europian ones,(like i said uniform) and the Saturn5 had to be transported by rail from the various manufactuers to the lanch pad. Therefor the Romans are crazy because they effected the size fo the rocket going to the moon more that 1000 years after they were no more.
